    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="842"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d842">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6176/12–2844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-28">December 28,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10759. For Bugbee from Haley. Following advisors to Haley selected for Rubber
                    Study Group meeting: Viles,<note n="50" xml:id="d842fn50">A. L. Viles,
                        President, Rubber Manufacturers Association, Inc.</note> Young,<note n="51"
                        xml:id="d842fn51">R. D. Young, President, Rubber Trade Association of New
                        York, Inc.</note> Collyer, Litchfield, Smith, Hotchkiss,<note n="52"
                        xml:id="d842fn52">H. Stuart Hotchkiss, Chairman, Cambridge Rubber Co.</note>
                        Firestone,<note n="53" xml:id="d842fn53">Harvey S. Firestone, Jr.,
                        President, Firestone Tire and Rubber Co.</note> Davis,<note n="54"
                        xml:id="d842fn54">F. B. Davis, Jr., Chairman, U.S. Rubber Co.</note>
                        Trimble<note n="55" xml:id="d842fn55">Gilbert K. Trimble, Mid West Rubber
                        Reclaiming Co.</note> from industry; Batt,<note n="56" xml:id="d842fn56"
                        >William L. Batt, Vice Chairman, War Production Board.</note> Bicknell,
                        Klossner<note n="57" xml:id="d842fn57">Howard J. Klossner, President, Rubber
                        Reserve Corp.</note> and Clark<note n="58" xml:id="d842fn58">James Clark,
                        Rubber Bureau, War Production Board.</note> from government. Secretariat
                    Phillips, DuBarry<note n="59" xml:id="d842fn59">Joseph N. DuBarry, member of the
                        Commodities Division of the Department.</note> and Bugbee. Post conference
                    trip to synthetic plants planned for January 29 to about February 2.</p>
                <p>Department will attempt to dispatch three copies of revised report in time to
                    reach London by January 8. Revised military tire ticket requires recomputation
                    of consumption data. [Haley.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
